\section{Human Evaluation}
\label{sec:human_eval}

To complement automated and LLM-based evaluation, we conducted a
human evaluation study with clinical domain experts across three
languages: \textbf{Hindi}, \textbf{Marathi}, and \textbf{Telugu}.
These languages were selected to span Indo-Aryan high-resource (Hindi),
Indo-Aryan medium-resource (Marathi), and Dravidian (Telugu) typological
groups, enabling assessment of whether automated metrics correlate with
human expert judgement across language families.

